{
  "doc_id": "47224",
  "text": "The influence of several per-and postoperative factors, such as the surgical approach used (cochleostomy or round window approach) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , the depth or angle of insertion of the electrode array [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , the number of active electrodes [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] , have already been addressed. However the samples were small leading to controversial results. The large sample size of 2251 patients in the present study offered the opportunity to investigate the influence of these factors on CI speech performance with greater certainty.",
